A lot of us are doing ‘dissolving clinics’ now. This can come with considerations.
CMAC place emphasis on respectful use of filler. Being careful not to overfill delicate facial structures, giving attention to technique and injection plane.
Prevention is better than the cure, and as we learn more about how our products behave, and where they are being placed we have a need to learn and better our practice.
Despite this we can inherit issues due to the trend of dissolving- we may not even have caused the issue.
We would urge caution to the following points in the post to support your practice when removing filler.

Thank you 🙏 laskinaesthetics  collagen keeps the skin in place while elastin allows it to return to its original shape.  We often hear about these two proteins in conjunction with each other because they work together to give skin its shape and firmness.
.
🏗️ COLLAGEN (THE FRAMEWORK) Collagen’s main purpose is to provide strength and rigidity to skin. They’re comprised of very strong fibers that have impressive tensile strength, and is the foundation upon which the outer layer of the skin is anchored.
.
🪃 ELASTIN (THE RUBBER BAND) Elastin is responsible for allowing skin to “snap back” to their original shape.  In fact, these proteins are five times more stretchable than a rubber band of the same diameter.
.
As we age, collagen becomes more cross-linked and rigid, resulting in a weaker framework for skin, so it caves and bends, forming wrinkles.
.
At the same time, we produce less elastin. The elastin we do have starts to lose its ability to snap back much like a rubber band being stretched a hundred times. This results in the sagging we see around the eyes, jaw line, and neck. #laskinaesthetics #pluryal

THR Medical Products, en su apuesta por una formación e información objetiva y de calidad, se presenta este año en el 38 Congreso Nacional SEME con un formato novedoso de charlas clínico-prácticas a lo largo de todo el congreso, que se impartirán en una Sala VIP con capacidad para 30 personas.
